# Git & PR Standards

## Commit Messages

Use present tense, imperative mood, start with a verb:

### Good Examples

```
Add Python SDK installation guide
Fix broken links in deployment section
Update API authentication examples
Remove deprecated configuration options
Refactor navigation structure
```

### Bad Examples

```
Added installation docs
Fixed links
Updates
WIP
changes
```

## Commit Structure

```
<type>: <subject>

[optional body]

[optional footer]
```

Types:
- `Add`: New content or features
- `Update`: Changes to existing content
- `Fix`: Bug fixes, broken links, typos
- `Remove`: Deleting content or files
- `Refactor`: Reorganizing without changing meaning
- `Docs`: Meta-documentation changes

## Pull Requests

### Before Opening a PR

- [ ] All tests pass (`mkdocs build --strict`)
- [ ] Changes reviewed in local preview
- [ ] Links verified
- [ ] Screenshots added (if UI changes)
- [ ] Branch is up to date with main

### PR Template

Use the template in `.github/PULL_REQUEST_TEMPLATE.md`:

- Fill out all sections
- Check all applicable boxes
- Include screenshots for visual changes
- Reference related issues: `Closes #123`, `Related to #456`
- Provide testing instructions

### PR Title Format

```
Add feature: Quick start guide for Python SDK
Fix: Broken links in API documentation
Update: Deployment configuration examples
```

### PR Description

Include:

1. **What**: What changes were made
2. **Why**: Why the changes were needed
3. **How**: How to test/verify the changes
4. **Screenshots**: Visual proof if applicable
5. **Related issues**: Link to issues

Example:

```markdown
## What
Added comprehensive Python SDK installation guide.

## Why
Users were confused about virtual environment setup and dependency management.

## How to Test
1. Navigate to SDK > Installation
2. Verify code examples render correctly
3. Check all links work

## Related Issues
Closes #42
```

## Branch Naming

Use descriptive branch names:

```
docs/add-python-sdk-guide
docs/update-api-auth
docs/fix-broken-links
docs/refactor-navigation
```

Format: `docs/<action>-<brief-description>`

## Review Process

### As a Contributor

- Respond to feedback promptly
- Make requested changes
- Resolve conversations when addressed
- Keep commits focused and clean

### As a Reviewer

- Check for technical accuracy
- Verify writing style matches guidelines
- Test links and code examples
- Ensure no sensitive information is included
- Approve when ready or request changes with clear feedback
